>>>>>
>>>>> Dear Mr. Sathishkumar,
>>>>>
>>>>> Please find below the clarifications for the IST Review Questions 
>>>>> pertaining to the FSD document:
>>>>>
>>>>> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>>>>>
>>>>> *1. Multiple Punches per Shift*
>>>>> *Clarification:*
>>>>> Multiple punches (In/Out) are considered to accurately capture 
>>>>> actual working time excluding break periods.
>>>>>
>>>>> *Example Logic:*
>>>>> Net Worked Time = (OutTime1 − InTime1) + (OutTime2 − InTime2)
>>>>> = 233 + 217 = 450 minutes
>>>>>
>>>>> Break Duration = 30 minutes (excluded from productive time)
>>>>>
>>>>> For a standard shift of 480 minutes with a 30-minute scheduled 
>>>>> break, the expected net working time is 450 minutes.
>>>>>
>>>>> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>>>>>
>>>>> *2. mac_ticketno vs ticketno*
>>>>> *Clarification:*
>>>>> In most mills, both values are identical. However, where 
>>>>> differences exist, a *mapping facility is available in the 
>>>>> Employee Master*to link /mac_ticketno/with /ticketno/.
>>>>>
>>>>> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>>>>>
>>>>> *3. Night Festival Holiday (NFH) Flag*
>>>>> *Clarification:*
>>>>> This is a *statutory requirement under the Tamil Nadu Shops and 
>>>>> Establishments Act*.
>>>>>
>>>>>   * If an employee works on NFH → Eligible for one additional day
>>>>>     salary (either OT or regular pay as per policy)
>>>>>   * If absent → Still eligible for NFH salary
>>>>>
>>>>> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>>>>>
>>>>> *4. Pr_DattExcept Table (Weekly-Off Attendance)*
>>>>> *Clarification:*
>>>>> Employees who work on weekly off are processed based on 
>>>>> mill-specific configuration:
>>>>>
>>>>>   * Either marked as *Present*, or
>>>>>   * Treated as *Overtime (OT)*
>>>>>
>>>>> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>>>>>
>>>>> *5. PostOT_AttnDwnd Flag*
>>>>> *Clarification:*
>>>>> OT calculated during attendance download is *provisional*.
>>>>>
>>>>> HR personnel are responsible for:
>>>>>
>>>>>   * Verification
>>>>>   * Modification (if required)
>>>>>     based on disciplinary or punch irregularities.
>>>>>
>>>>> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>>>>>
>>>>> *6. Attendance Lock (PR_AttendanceOTLock)*
>>>>> *Clarification:*
>>>>> Attendance locking is performed by the *HR Admin*after verifying 
>>>>> and reconciling daily attendance records.
>>>>>
>>>>> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>>>>>
>>>>> *7. KSP_AttendanceTransferDate (Stored Procedure)*
>>>>> *Clarification:*
>>>>> This procedure performs *day-by-day replication of attendance 
>>>>> logic*, ensuring consistency with transactional calculations.
>>>>>
>>>>> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>>>>>
>>>>> *8. Actual Shift vs Scheduled Shift (ActShift)*
>>>>> *Clarification:*
>>>>> Differences occur when employees work on *weekly off or 
>>>>> non-scheduled days*.
>>>>>
>>>>>   * ActShift is *derived from shift setup*based on actual In/Out
>>>>>     punches
>>>>>   * It is not directly captured from the biometric device
>>>>>
>>>>> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>>>>>
>>>>> *9. Half-Day Threshold Formula*
>>>>> *Clarification:*
>>>>> The half-day and full-day eligibility criteria are 
>>>>> *customer-configurable*within the Shift Setup:
>>>>>
>>>>>   * “Half Day From”
>>>>>   * “Full Day From”
>>>>>
>>>>> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>>>>>
>>>>> *10. modifiedon Protection*
>>>>> *Clarification:*
>>>>> Manually edited records in *Pr_Datt*are overwritten during 
>>>>> updates; however:
>>>>>
>>>>>   * All modifications are *logged within the ERP system*
>>>>>   * Manual correction is performed through the *attendance
>>>>>     correction interface*
>>>>>
>>>>> ------------------------------------------------------------------------
>>>>>
>>>>> Kindly review the above clarifications and provide your feedback.
>>>>>
>>>>> Thanks & Regards,
>>>>> *V. Palanivel*
